HEADWORD: Agriculture
<hw>Ag"ri*cul`ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>agricultura</ets>; <ets>ager</ets> field + <ets>cultura</ets>
cultivation: cf. F. <ets>agriculture</ets>. See <er>Acre</er> and
<er>Culture</er>.]</ety> <def>The art or science of cultivating the
ground, including the harvesting of crops, and the rearing and
management of live stock; tillage; husbandry; farming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

